HEADWORD: Sulphonal
<hw>Sul"pho*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A substance employed as a hypnotic, produced by the union of
mercaptan and acetone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

